    "Evaluation CriteriaTo evaluate the performance of our multimodal fusion algorithm, we utilized the F1 Score (F 1-Score), also known as the F1 Measure, and an accuracy metric called Acc-2.",
    "These are defined as follows:F 1 = 2T P 2T P + F N + F P (15)Acc i = T P i T P i + F P i(16)Here, T P denotes the number of true positive observations, F P represents the number of false positive observations, and F N stands for the number of false negative observations.",
    "Moreover, we considered the F1 Score as a harmonic mean of precision and recall, with Acc-2 being a binary accuracy excluding the neutral class; i.e., a score of 0.",
    "Additionally, the Mean Absolute Error (MAE) and the Correlation Coefficient (Corr) were employed for a more nuanced understanding of the results:M AE(x, h) = 1 m m i=1 ∥h(x i) -y i ∥(17)We evaluated metrics such as the F1 score, Acc, and Corr, while computational costs were gauged using the MAE and the number of parameters, and parameter count.These metrics and cost measures provide a comprehensive view of the algorithm's performance and its operational demands.",
    "BaselineIo thoroughly evaluate the overall performance of our model, we conducted a fair comparison with leading multimodal emotion recognition models.Tensor Fusion Network (TFN) [23]: TFN leverages the Cartesian product to calculate tensors from each modality, effectively capturing unimodal, bimodal, and trimodal interaction information.Low-rank Multimodal Fusion (LMF) [24]: As an advancement over TFN, LMF aims to reduce computational complexity and enhance efficiency through low-rank tensor factorization."
